Reasoning: 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the most likely category as the paper deals with information extraction and concept mining from personal data. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes an approach for bootstrapping semantic services using machine learning techniques. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of a graphical user interface for user feedback and interaction. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper deals with the creation of a knowledge graph from personal data. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also relevant as the paper proposes a machine learning approach for concept mining.
